3. **Molecular Cooling Threshold Analysis**: Calculate the expected halo mass function for molecular cooling halos ($T_{vir} < 10^4$ K) at $z \approx 2-4$. Compare the Sparkler GC mass distribution ($10^6 - 10^7 M_{\odot}$) against this theoretical mass range to determine if the Sparkler clusters are consistent with formation in smaller, molecular-cooling-dominated environments.

